AGI - Al Capone's "tree", a 45 semi-automatic Colt, will auction for a figure that could reach the three million dollars. The gun belonged to one of America's most famous gangsters, and he himself called "sweetheart>", "tree", will be sold to the highest bidder on May 18 by the auction house Richmond, South Carolina. This is the Colt who, according to his family, saved Al Capone's life more than once. Built in 1911, he accompanied for almost all his life the gangster, whose real name was Alphonse Gabriel Capone, known as "Scarface", born in Brooklyn in 1899 and became the symbol of organized crime in the United States. At Capone, he was the head of a mafia dome that managed gambling, smuggling and lace in the years of prohibition.
<br The gun is considered a collector's piece, whose value should range between two and three million. After the death of the boss, on January 25, 1947, at the age of 48, after spending a lot of time in prison, and developed dementia caused by syphilis, the gun passed to his wife, Mae, who in turn gave it to his son, Sonny Capone. The gun would then pass to one of the daughters, Diane and Barbara, after Sonny's death in 2004. The two gangster grandchildren had auctioned the weapon in 2021, when the Colt ended up with another two hundred heaps belonging to the grandfather and sold for a million dollars.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
At the time, Diane Capone told Cbs: "This weapon was a kind of personal protection and I think it saved his life several times. That's why he called her "tesorò". Capone always brought her with him. The decision to auction it had drawn criticism from those who accused their daughters of wanting to earn a fortune from the criminal reputation of their grandfather. Others now believe that the gun is a collector's object, it represents a historical piece > and also a part of the life of gangsters and psychology of a symbol of American gangsterism >. Thinking of that faithful Colt, Capone once said: "You get more with a kind word and a weapon that only with a kind word." And in his "tree", the boss had found his best companion. In case someone is interested, the auction base will start from $500 thousand>.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

